      it is grappled (escape DC 17). Until this grapple ends, the target is restrained,
      and the remorhaz can''t bite another target. '
    category: Actions
  - name: Swallow.
    value: ' The remorhaz makes one bite attack against a Medium or smaller creature
      it is grappling. If the attack hits, that creature takes the bite''s damage
      and is swallowed, and the grapple ends. While swallowed, the creature is blinded
      and restrained, it has total cover against attacks and other effects outside
      the remorhaz, and it takes 21 (6d6) acid damage at the start of each of the
      remorhaz''s turns.'
    category: Actions
  - name: other
    value: f the remorhaz takes 30 damage or more on a single turn from a creature
      inside it, the remorhaz must succeed on a DC 15 Constitution saving throw at
      the end of that turn or regurgitate all swallowed creatures, which fall prone
      in a space within 10 feet of the remorhaz. If the remorhaz dies, a swallowed
